Xi Jinping sends congratulatory letter to 2021 Greater Bay Area Science Forum - Xinhua Xinhua News Agency, Beijing, Dec. 11 (Xinhua) -- President Xi Jinping sent a congratulatory letter to the 2021 Greater Bay Area Science Forum on Dec. 11. Xi Jinping pointed out that the world today is experiencing a major change unprecedented in a century, global science and technology innovation has entered an intensive and active period, and a new round of scientific and technological revolution and industrial change has a profound impact on the global economic structure. Guangdong, Hong Kong, Macao and the Greater Bay Area should focus on building an international science and technology innovation center strategic positioning, and strive to build a global science and technology innovation highland and promote the development of new industries. China is willing to work with scientists from all over the world and international scientific and technological organizations to closely exchange and cooperate in international science and technology, strengthen research on major scientific issues, promote common scientific and technological breakthroughs, deepen collaboration on key scientific projects, and jointly promote the development of the world's scientific endeavors for the betterment of mankind. 2021 Greater Bay Area Science Forum opened in Guangzhou, Guangdong Province on the same day, with the theme "Exploring the Future, Sharing Science", hosted by the Guangdong Provincial People's Government.
